</div> 
<p><strong>Serpent-Hunter</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Great Spears" href="/Great+Spears" target="">Great Spear</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Serpent-Hunter</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>. It is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for attacking enemies at a long reach and does not require any stats value.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Weapon that serves as both greatsword and spear. Thought to<br>have been used to hunt an immortal great serpent in the distant<br>past, it manifests a long blade of light when facing such a creature.</em></p> 
 <p><em>When their master's heroic aspirations degenerated into mere<br>greed, his men searched for a weapon with which they might halt<br>their lord.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Serpent-Hunter in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Serpent-Hunter weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Held by a corpse on the left as you enter the boss chamber of <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Rykard, Lord of Blasphemy" href="/Rykard,+Lord+of+Blasphemy" target="">Rykard, Lord of Blasphemy</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=4103&amp;lat=-86.720312&amp;lng=66.330933&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=4103&amp;lat=-86.720312&amp;lng=66.330933&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
 <li>If the players picks up the Serpent-Hunter in the middle of being summoned. After picking up the spear and getting summoned, a second copy of the Serpent-Hunter would appear at the original location upon returning to their world, allowing&nbsp;you to dual wield the Serpent-Hunters.</li> 
 <li>This weapon will not be respawned on a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring New Game Plus" href="/New+Game+Plus">New Game Plus</a>.&nbsp;The only way to respawn the weapon is to discard it. After discarding the weapon and reloading your location, the weapon would reappear at its original location provided that <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Rykard, Lord of Blasphemy" href="/Rykard,+Lord+of+Blasphemy">Rykard, Lord of Blasphemy</a> was still alive.</li> 
 <li>If the player manages to beat <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Rykard, Lord of Blasphemy" href="/Rykard,+Lord+of+Blasphemy">Rykard, Lord of Blasphemy</a> without picking up the Serpent-Hunter, the weapon disappears.</li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Video Location" href="https://youtu.be/gjx27iqiG8c?t=5090">Video Location</a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Serpent-Hunter Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Great-Serpent Hunt" href="/Great-Serpent+Hunt" target="">Great-Serpent Hunt</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon can<strong>not</strong> be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Serpent-Hunter</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>A solid weapon for Strength build due to its A scaling for Strength. While slightly heavier than the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Lance" href="/Lance">Lance</a> and cannot be infused with Ashes of War, the Serpent-Hunter has a horizontal sweep&nbsp;as its strong attacks. It can also be used as an offhand weapon for the Lance if one wants to dual wield Great Spear class weapons.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;0 
  <ul> 
   <li>This item cannot be sold.</li> 
   <li>This item cannot be dropped and given to another player.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
</ul> 
<p>Regarding the weapon's special properties while fighting <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring God-Devouring Serpent" href="/God-Devouring+Serpent">God-Devouring Serpent</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Rykard, Lord of Blasphemy" href="/Rykard,+Lord+of+Blasphemy">Rykard, Lord of Blasphemy</a>:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>The weapon's attacks, and its weapon skill, will generate additional beams of swirling wind that greatly extend its range to allow the player to hit Rykard from outside the lava pool at his feet.</li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Axe Talisman" href="/Axe+Talisman">Axe Talisman</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spiked Cracked Tear" href="/Spiked+Cracked+Tear">Spiked Cracked Tear</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Claw Talisman" href="/Claw+Talisman">Claw Talisman</a> (and by extension, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Raptor's Black Feathers" href="/Raptor's+Black+Feathers">Raptor's Black Feathers</a>), <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Twinblade Talisman" href="/Twinblade+Talisman">Twinblade Talisman</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spear Talisman" href="/Spear+Talisman">Spear Talisman</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Curved Sword Talisman" href="/Curved+Sword+Talisman">Curved Sword Talisman</a> <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>do</strong></span> <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>not</strong></span> affect the special damage of the weapon.</li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Warrior Jar Shard" href="/Warrior+Jar+Shard">Warrior Jar Shard</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Shard of Alexander" href="/Shard+of+Alexander">Shard of Alexander</a>&nbsp;<strong>does</strong> boost the damage of the weapon's Skill. 
  <ul> 
   <li>Because of the long windup of the skill, people can believe that <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Godfrey Icon" href="/Godfrey+Icon">Godfrey Icon</a> boost its damage, but that is<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong> not</strong> </span>the case.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ritual Sword Talisman" href="/Ritual+Sword+Talisman">Ritual Sword Talisman</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Red-Feathered Branchsword" href="/Red-Feathered+Branchsword">Red-Feathered Branchsword</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Kindred of Rot's Exultation" href="/Kindred+of+Rot's+Exultation">Kindred of Rot's Exultation</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Lord of Blood's Exultation" href="/Lord+of+Blood's+Exultation">Lord of Blood's Exultation</a> work as normal, and provide a general damage boost. The same applies to the incantation <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Flame Grant me Strength" href="/Flame+Grant+me+Strength">Flame, Grant me Strength</a>.</li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Winged Sword Insignia" href="/Winged+Sword+Insignia">Winged Sword Insignia</a> does <span style="text-decoration: underline;">not trigger</span> while attacking, but does<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> receive the benefit</span> if triggered by another weapon.</li> 
 <li>When dual wielding with another Great Spear class weapon, both spears will generate the beams during the powerstance attacks.</li> 
</ul> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Serpent-Hunter</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Serpent-Hunter Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Serpent-Hunter Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></p> 
<p>This upgrade can't be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;or boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
