				<li id="16754093" class="cmnt-root" data="6" data-d="1660183391000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578183/Serpent-Hunter" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">10 Aug 2022 22:03</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16754093" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Hands down best greatspear for strength builds. Massive damage, great moveset and looks fine as hell. Skill is situational but does tremendous damage if you manage to land it, you can bait people into the second part which comes out surprisingly fast. Here&apos;s a few interesting things I&apos;ve noticed while using this weapon: The rolling/crouch attack is different from all the other greatspears, it&apos;s the colossal sword poke which is a nice bonus to an already great moveset. Second thing, all of its attacks are considered pierce attacks, even the R2 sweeps and jumping R2 so you&apos;ll greatly benefit from the spear Talisman.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16754093" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16754093" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>7</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span><