				<li id="16714462" class="cmnt-root" data="19" data-d="1655184149000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578183/Serpent-Hunter" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">14 Jun 2022 01:22</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16714462" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">You can get 2 of these if you do this:<br/><br/>You need to invade or get summoned for co-op in the room right before the arena. Then, as soon as the invasion or summon message pops up on screen, run into your arena and grab the Serpent Hunter. You should be able to grab it right before leaving your world (sometimes you&apos;ll have a lot more time, depending on internet).<br/><br/>In the other player&apos;s world, do what you like - leave right away if you want to, fight them, or help them with the boss because you&apos;re a nice and good furled finger. After the session, when you appear back in your world, you&apos;ll spawn in the room before the arena. So, run back into the arena and grab your SECOND Serpent Hunter! Have fun :)<br/><br/>What&apos;s happening is the game saves your state before entering a multiplayer session, but since you were in a boss arena when the session started, it puts you back outside and respawns the spear, allowing you to grab another.<br/><br/>Credit to u/FuryForged</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16714462" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt